Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Halve,
peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}.
Mince @parsley{1/4}(minced) leaves and stems. Remove @Italian pork sausage{9} from
casings; discard casings.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add onion, bell pepper, and half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1/2}. Cook, stirring,
until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add sausage and another drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} to the pan. Cook, breaking
up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Once sausage is cooked through, add @diced tomatoes{14%oz can} to pan. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, and remaining @Tuscan Heat Spice{1/2}. Bring to a boil, then
lower heat and let simmer while spaghetti cooks. After you've drained spaghetti,
stir @chicken stock concentrate{1} and 3/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water
into pan. Continue simmering until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Add spaghetti to pan; toss to coat. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp}, half the parsley, and
half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}. Season with salt and pepper. Divide between
bowls and sprinkle with remaining parsley and Parmesan.

> If pasta seems dry, add more reserved pasta cooking water as needed. 